<subSubSection lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="404" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,1664,2015]" lastBlockId="3.[151,1436,151,321]" lastPageId="3" lastPageNumber="404" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1737,1763]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species was originally described based on both male and female specimens but a female from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,246,1772,1798]" name="Pakistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
“Layallpur [Faisalabad], 
<collectingRegion box="[535,616,1772,1798]" country="Pakistan" name="Punjab" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Punjab</collectingRegion>
, at light; 10.X.29 (Coll. A. Rahman)” (ZSI), was listed as the “ 
<typeStatus box="[1323,1426,1772,1798]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">holotype</typeStatus>
” together with “four other specimens from the type locality and numerous specimens from several other localities in the Indian Museum collection”. The specimens other than the female 
<typeStatus box="[938,1036,1844,1870]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">holotype</typeStatus>
may be considered 
<typeStatus box="[1262,1369,1845,1871]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">paratypes</typeStatus>
but it is not clear from which specimen the male genitalia were figured and the male genitalia slide is now missing (pers. com. C. Viraktamath). Therefore, Pruthi’s figure of the male could be from a specimen either from 
<collectingCountry box="[1270,1365,1916,1942]" name="Pakistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
or 
<collectingCountry name="India" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">India</collectingCountry>
. No further material of this species from 
<collectingCountry box="[657,752,1952,1978]" name="Pakistan" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">Pakistan</collectingCountry>
has been studied since the original description and although the original material was examined by 
<bibRefCitation author="Dash, P. C. &amp; Viraktamath, C. A." box="[602,925,1988,2015]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403" pagination="1 - 59" refId="ref7387" refString="Dash, P. C. &amp; Viraktamath, C. A. (1998) A review of the Indian and Nepalese grass feeding leafhopper genus Deltocephalus (Recilia) (Homoptera: Cicadellidae) with description of new species. Hexapoda, 10 (1 &amp; 2), 1 - 59." type="journal article" year="1998">Dash &amp; Viraktamath (1998)</bibRefCitation>
, including a male 
<typeStatus box="[1141,1240,1989,2015]" pageId="2" pageNumber="403">paratype</typeStatus>
, their figures are from their Indian specimens (pers. com. C. Viraktamath). Despite the above uncertainties, assuming that the female 
<typeStatus box="[151,249,187,213]" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">holotype</typeStatus>
and the male specimen illustrated by Pruthi are conspecific, the identity of the species is clear based on the aedeagus with a distinctive large subapical ventral process (
<figureCitation box="[865,951,223,249]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1085,1109]" captionTargetBox="[158,1430,346,1054]" captionTargetId="figure-105@3.[151,1436,342,1059]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 1. Maiestas species.A–D, M. albomaculata (Dash &amp; Viraktamath) (after Naveed et al., 2019) A: habitus, dorsal view; B: face; C: connective and aedeagus, dorsal view; D: connective and aedeagus, lateral view; E, M. indica (Singh-Pruthi) (after Dash &amp; Viraktamath, 1998): connective and aedeagus, lateral view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5635914" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5635914/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Fig. 1E</figureCitation>
). The species can also be recognized by its accessary forewing cross-veins, similar to 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Metcalf" baseAuthorityYear="1967" box="[631,745,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Maiestas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pruthii">
<emphasis box="[631,654,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">M</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[669,745,259,285]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">pruthii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[801,964,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Maiestas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undefined-1">
<emphasis box="[801,902,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Maiestas</emphasis>
sp. 1
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[1020,1184,259,285]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Maiestas" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="404" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="undefined-2">
<emphasis box="[1020,1121,259,284]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="404">Maiestas</emphasis>
sp. 2
</taxonomicName>
, but from these it also differs by its shorter head as shown in Pruthi’s original figure.
</paragraph>
